\fs44 \cf4 5-6 large apples\uc0\u8232 1 lemon, juiced\u8232 1/4 cup granulated sugar\u8232 1/4 cup flour\u8232 1 teaspoon cinnamon\u8232 1/4 teaspoon cardamom\u8232 Topping:\u8232 1 stick butter, softened\u8232 1/2 cup rolled oats\u8232 1/2 cup flour \u8232 1/2 cup brown sugar\u8232 1 teaspoon cinnamon\u8232 1/2 teaspoon cardamom\u8232 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger\u8232 pinch of salt\u8232 \u8232 Preheat your oven to 350\'b0 F. Start with the apples. Peel them all and slice them thinly, placing them in a large bowl. Squeeze the lemon juice over them and toss to prevent browning. Then add the granulated sugar, 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon cardamom and mix it together well, evenly coating the apples. In a separate bowl mix together the butter, oats, flour, brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon cardamom, the ground ginger and a pinch of salt for good measure. Mash it all up until it\'92s sticky and clumpy.\u8232 \u8232 Lightly grease the inside of a 2-quart baking dish with butter or cooking spray. Dump in your cinnamon apples. Pour on your topping mix and evenly cover the apples. Place in the oven and bake for 1 hour or until apples are nice and soft and top starts to turn more of a golden brown. Remove from oven and serve with your favorite brand of vanilla ice cream and caramel sauce. Caramel sauce is not optional. It is essential.
